# CODEOWNERS for digital-school-gitops
#
# Philosophy: review is required only for paths that touch many envs at
# once OR are production-sensitive. Daily lab iteration (lab/dev,
# lab/test, runbooks, docs, image-tag bumps from CI) is direct-push
# allowed — no required reviewer. This keeps friction low for solo
# operator work while preserving review discipline on the blast-radius
# paths.
#
# Doc reference: Phase 1 Roadmap §2.4 L7 — "Staging requires PR approval
# + CODEOWNERS; No direct commits to staging branch". Applied per-path.
#
# NOTE: no top-level '*' catch-all → paths not listed below have NO
# required reviewer and can be direct-pushed.

# lab/staging — production-like release gate
/lab/staging/ @ariefnugrahaaa

# prod/* — every path touches live users
/prod/blue/ @ariefnugrahaaa
/prod/green/ @ariefnugrahaaa
/prod/routing/ @ariefnugrahaaa

# base/ — changes propagate to every environment at once
/base/ @ariefnugrahaaa

# cluster-policies/ — VAP / admission rules. Misconfig can brick the cluster
/cluster-policies/ @ariefnugrahaaa

# argocd/ — Application manifests. Changes here wire the whole gitops system
/argocd/ @ariefnugrahaaa

# platform/ — shared platform add-ons (cert-manager, ingress-system, monitoring)
/platform/ @ariefnugrahaaa

# CI + gh configs
/.github/ @ariefnugrahaaa

# Freely pushable (NOT in the list, kept here as a reminder):
#   /lab/dev/         daily iteration
#   /lab/test/        intermediate env
#   /runbooks/        operator docs
#   /docs/            narrative docs
#   README.md, etc.
